article.headline: Albany (NY) 72, Hartford 60
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. -- Logan Aronhalt scored 17 points, including the game-winner, and Albany held Hartford scoreless for the final 5:02 to erase a four-point deficit and win 72-60 Saturday. The Great Danes (14-9, 6-3 America East Conference), who won their second straight game, led 43-34 when the Hawks (4-17, 4-5) used a 10-0 run to pull ahead. Albany regained the lead on a layup by John Puk, building a seven-point cushion with 9:44 left. Hartford answered with a 16-5 spurt to lead 60-56, but could not score in the final 5 minutes, missing eight shots, six from beyond the arc. After Jayson Guerrier's 3, Aronhalt scored nine of Albany's last 13 points, including the go-ahead jumper with 3:56 left. Gerardo Suero added 14 points and Mike Black 10 for the Great Danes, who also beat the Hawks 88-63 on Jan. 2. Andres Torres scored 18 to lead Hartford, which has lost three straight.
